records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jason W Kohl in court, in custody, with attorney Katie Elizabeth Babe.   Andrea M Will appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 YEARS 6 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 0 days if sentence credit is requested and granted by Court to be applied to Count #1 if revoked) Commencing forthwith;
  -  1 YEAR 6 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling; (or any other activity deemed appropriate by agent;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Perform 100 Hours Community Service TOTAL.

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (apply cash bail);

CONDITION TIME: 1 YEAR - the first 30 days to be served straight time.  The balance of condition time is stayed for the Defendant  to participate in inpatient treatment at Rosecrance followed by sober living house. The Defendant is only to be released from jail for direct admittance into Rosecrance after the initial 30 days straight time and upon completion of Rosecrance the defendant to reside at a sober living house.  If sober living house is not available upon completion of Rosecrance the defendant is to be housed in custody at the Waukesha County Huber Facility until sober living house becomes available. 

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.


Count #3:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 YEARS 6 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 0 days) (consecutive to Count #1);
  -  1 YEAR 6 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  See Count #1;

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid as a condition of probation);

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given
